result.execSummary:
The defendant Jacob L Engel was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Retail Theft - Intentionally Conceal (>$500 - $5000), a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.50(1m)(d).
  • Possession of Controlled Substance, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(b).
  • Possession of Controlled Substance, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(b).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

[MK] case called at 3:14pm. 
Defendant Jacob L Engel in court with Attorney Sylvie Dahnert.   ADA Brookellen Teuber appears for the State of Wisconsin.
ADA Teuber verifies victim rights compliance. 
Maximum penalties recited; Constitutional rights reviewed; plea of " Guilty " entered on Counts #1 & #2 & #3; factual basis stipulated; the Court accepts the pleas, finds the Defendant guilty, and orders Judgment of Conviction entered.

On Motion of the State, the Court reads-in and dismisses Count #4.

On Counts #1, #2, #3 each, the Court withholds sentence, and places Mr. Engel on Probation for two years, with conditions:
--to undergo AODA assessment, treatment and follow through 
--to undergo any other assessment, treatment or counseling as required by the Agent
--to attempt to obtain/maintain employment and/or education program as approved by the Agent
--to maintain absolute sobriety:  no possession or consumption of alcohol;  no possession or ingestion of controlled substances without a valid prescription 
--to only take prescription medications only as prescribed
--no presence in bars, taverns, package houses
--to submit to drug and alcohol testing per the Agent 
--to comply with DNA sample provision 
--to pay costs, fees, assessments and surcharges, including the DNA surcharge  

Days credit for time already served:  2 days
Felony firearm prohibition warnings are given 
The Cash Bail amount is to be applied toward payment of court financial obligations.
The Court requires Mr. Engel to report to the Probation Office by 4:00pm tomorrow [5/3/17].  
recess 3:41pm.
